        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer322208640" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9889329468978015283">I read this book when I was about ten years old. My grandmother was a missionary in India andshe used to give me &apos;improving&apos; books to read - this being one of them. Luckily my grandmother had extremely good taste in literature and every &apos;improving&apos; book she gave me was also immensely readable as this one is. I was especially keen on Gladys Aylward as she was as the title says a small woman. As am I - her story is an inspiration to anyone who may feel that they are too small or insignificant to m</span>
  <span id="freeText9889329468978015283" style="display:none">I read this book when I was about ten years old. My grandmother was a missionary in India andshe used to give me 'improving' books to read - this being one of them. Luckily my grandmother had extremely good taste in literature and every 'improving' book she gave me was also immensely readable as this one is. I was especially keen on Gladys Aylward as she was as the title says a small woman. As am I - her story is an inspiration to anyone who may feel that they are too small or insignificant to make a difference in the world. Maybe we can't all make such heroic differences but we can all make a positive contribution in some way. This book taught me that lesson.</span>
