        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3405391524" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4216342338363093480">This is the story of Gladys Alyward, missionary to China. <br/><br/>After being rejected by a London missionary society, Gladys decided to get to China under her own steam, because she believed it is where God wanted her to be. Working several domestic jobs (sometimes simultaneously) she eventually saved enough money for her long passage into the heart of Northern China. After she got there Japan invaded during World War 2 and Gladys led a couple of hundred orphans on foot through treacherous, Japanese oc</span>
  <span id="freeText4216342338363093480" style="display:none">This is the story of Gladys Alyward, missionary to China. <br /><br />After being rejected by a London missionary society, Gladys decided to get to China under her own steam, because she believed it is where God wanted her to be. Working several domestic jobs (sometimes simultaneously) she eventually saved enough money for her long passage into the heart of Northern China. After she got there Japan invaded during World War 2 and Gladys led a couple of hundred orphans on foot through treacherous, Japanese occupied terrain to get them to safety.<br /><br />A well written, thrilling, easy to read story by Alan Burgess that was the foundation for the classic film, The Inn of the Sixth Happiness. The book goes into much more detail and doesn't omit the Christian elements. (Oh. And doesn't have a romance with Kurt Jurgens.) I enjoyed it even more than the film and I enjoyed the film a-plenty.<br /><br />This one is truly an adventure story depicting the life of this amazing lady. Well worth your time and fits perfectly into my belief that "ordinary people can do amazing things in the hands of an EXTRA-ordinary God." (Do I need quotation marks when I quote myself?)<br /><br />Thank you for reading my review and considering this book.<br /><br />Sincerely, Laura-Lee</span>
