    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2654773002" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3750023555021969119">This is an extraordinary true story of a young woman, Gladys Aylward (1902-1970) who was impressed to leave her home in England and follow a deep desire within her heart, despite averse circumstances, to become a missionary in China. Anyone who reads her story will be genuinely inspired by her focus and determination to persevere amidst much suffering through inconvenience, discomfort, setbacks, and many situations that seemed utterly impossible. Her story is masterfully told by Alan Burgess who</span>
  <span id="freeText3750023555021969119" style="display:none">This is an extraordinary true story of a young woman, Gladys Aylward (1902-1970) who was impressed to leave her home in England and follow a deep desire within her heart, despite averse circumstances, to become a missionary in China. Anyone who reads her story will be genuinely inspired by her focus and determination to persevere amidst much suffering through inconvenience, discomfort, setbacks, and many situations that seemed utterly impossible. Her story is masterfully told by Alan Burgess who interviewed her for his radio program despite her initial response that she had not really done much with her life. I heard a missions professor at Moody Bible Institute once answer the question “who do you think was the greatest missionary ever?” by saying “probably the missionaries whose names we will never know.” This profound statement seems even more note worthy as I recognize how the story of Gladys Aylward could so easily have been unnoticed and unrecorded.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3750023555021969119" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


