              <span id="reviewTextContainer3117178633" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3120560563374253608">Very interesting story about a simple, short woman who left England in the 1930s to travel via the Trans-Siberian Railroad to China--where she presented herself, poor, uneducated and untrained, to be a missionary 1000 miles west of the ocean.<br/><br/>As usual, it was a tumultuous time in China, but relying on her faith and understanding of how the Holy Spirit worked, she presented herself as a living body for God&apos;s work.<br/><br/>I love how this story describes recognizing the leading of the Holy Spirit. It was in</span>
  <span id="freeText3120560563374253608" style="display:none">Very interesting story about a simple, short woman who left England in the 1930s to travel via the Trans-Siberian Railroad to China--where she presented herself, poor, uneducated and untrained, to be a missionary 1000 miles west of the ocean.<br /><br />As usual, it was a tumultuous time in China, but relying on her faith and understanding of how the Holy Spirit worked, she presented herself as a living body for God's work.<br /><br />I love how this story describes recognizing the leading of the Holy Spirit. It was informative, surprising, entertaining and enthralling. An excellent first read--albeit written 60+ years ago--for the new year.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3120560563374253608" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

